===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はこ|alt=函,筥,匣,筐,篋}}
{{swp|ja:}}
{{swp|Box}}

{{IPAchar|/pako/}} → {{IPAchar|/fako/}} → {{IPAchar|/hako/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}} ''pako''. First attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|箱・筥・函・篋・匣}}</ref> In turn, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*pako}}.

This term originally referred to a kind of [[wicker]] [[basket]] or [[box]] introduced from continental Asia, and the word is thought to be a borrowing from, or cognate with, a predecessor form of modern {{cog|ko|바구니||basket}}.<ref name="N">{{R:Nipponica}}</ref><ref name="SDHJ">{{R:Sekai Dai Hyakka Jiten}}</ref> Compare {{cog|okm|바고니〮|tr=pàkwòní}}.{{attention|okm|wrong hangeul}}

